content:
The List Merge Action merges multiple lists by matching values of specified list item JSON nodes. A basic merge matches node names exactly, while an advanced merge matches nodes that have different names and/or reside at different levels in the incoming lists.

To match nodes that have different names and/or reside at different levels, click Advanced Merge and specify settings for the nodes to be matched:

* List Key: Enter the name of the JSON list node where the node to be matched resides.
* Matching Path: Enter the path within the list to the node to be matched.
* Matching Group: Specify the same number for all nodes you want to match.

For older versions, use the Normalize Key setting instead of Matching Group, and specify the same key for each matching node. This key is only for matching and doesn't appear in the output.

Examples include:

* Basic list merge
* Advanced list merge
* List merge with dynamic output fields
title: List Merge Action for Integration Procedures
